description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust Staff Bank &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bank Doctor: Emergency Medicine ST3+&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Staff Bank Department is a dedicated team providing support to Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust across all staff groups. The Staff Bank strives to support our Hospitals with competent, reliable and registered workers who are able to provide the highest level of service to our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;More than just a healthcare provider, Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust is on a mission to give our patients exemplary, compassionate and safe care. We&#39;re doing this through innovations in patient care, education and research. Every day our people work hard to bring us closer to where we want to be. Join us and you’ll be part of a community that recognises your contribution – and inspires you to achieve great things.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Five London hospitals make up Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust. We are one of the largest Trusts in the country, we are also the UK&#39;s first academic health science centre (AHSC), bringing together the benefits of cutting-edge research with high standards of patient care. With more than 50 specialties and one of the largest portfolios of services in the country, we are a place full of opportunity as well as inspiration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Emergency Department bank doctor, you would become a Trust worker and have the flexibility to work when you want and where you prefer, from one of the two units in central London; St Mary’s Hospital and Charing Cross Hospital. Our rates of pay are competitive and we pay weekly on a Friday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bank Doctor: Emergency Medicine ST3+&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are recruiting for qualified Bank Doctors in Emergency Medicine ST3+wishing to work flexibly with our Staff Bank. By joining the Staff Bank you put yourself top of the list for any shifts requiring extra staff throughout the Trust. We have a variety of standard day shifts, late shifts, long day shifts and night shifts. Lines of work may also be available, should this be of interest.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working Bank shifts is easy:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are able to book shifts online via Patchwork or you can contact our dedicated bookings team via phone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits for you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Efficient recruitment process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complimentary core skills training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free required PPE provided&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can browse and book your own shifts on Patchwork&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have priority to book the shifts that you want – work when and where you like.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexibility of shift times and locations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive pay rates with weekly payment for the shifts you have worked&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS pension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Electronic timesheets, making your pay fast and on time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can view your shifts on Patchwork&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great opportunity to progress within the Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust and gain experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Friendly team environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lines of work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;All sites have easy access to various transport links&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free Trust hopper to commute between sites&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trust ID; enabling access to multiple offers and discounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your attributes and skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;GMC registered with a Licence to Practice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;FRCEM Primary or equivalent desirable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced Life support course&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 12 months Emergency Medicine experience of which at least 6 months in the NHS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage a wide range of ED presentations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have excellent written and verbal communication and interpersonal skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good IT skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand the importance of maintaining patient safety and minimising risk in accordance with Trust policy and procedure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate a good understanding of the importance of supportive and flexible team working&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to supervise junior colleagues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Eligible to work in the UK.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contact &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contact our recruitment team to start the process on &lt;strong&gt;0208 167 2493&lt;/strong&gt; or &lt;strong&gt;imperial.locums.admin@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;IMPORTANT:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please ensure you check your emails regularly as this is how we will communicate with you throughout the recruitment process. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
